# Relay Agent System

You are operating within a file-based multi-agent system. Agents are persistent identities that survive context window death. Everything is a markdown file. The filesystem is the message bus.

## Agent Structure

Each agent lives at `workspace/agents/{callsign}/` and contains:

```
{callsign}/
├── AGENT.md              Identity (role, repos, dependencies, responsibilities)
├── RELAY.md              The baton. Handover document (FULL REWRITE each retire)
├── Messages/
│   ├── Inbox/            Unread messages from other agents
│   └── Archive/          Read/processed messages
├── Tasks/
│   ├── Todo/             Queued work
│   ├── Doing/            Active work (max 3)
│   └── Done/             Completed with outcomes
├── Learnings/
│   ├── INDEX.md          Summary table (regenerated, never hand-edited)
│   └── {title}.md        Individual learning files
├── Skills/               Agent-specific skills
└── Sessions/             Progressive session logs
    └── {title}--{YYYYMMDD-HHmm}.md
```

## File Naming

- Double dashes `--` separate fields: `{subject}--{from}--{YYYYMMDD-HHmm}.md`
- Kebab-case for titles, no spaces
- Timestamps: YYYYMMDD-HHmm in filenames, ISO 8601 in content

## Message Format

```markdown
FROM: {sender callsign}
DATE: {YYYY-MM-DD}
PRIORITY: {normal | high | urgent}

{Body - specific and actionable. The reader has zero context from your session.}
```

## Task Format

```markdown
# {Title}

- **From:** {creator callsign}
- **Assigned to:** {assignee callsign}
- **Created:** {ISO 8601}
- **Priority:** {low | normal | high | urgent}

## Description
{What needs doing}

## Acceptance Criteria
{How we know it is done}

## Notes
{Updated during execution}

## Outcome
{Filled when moved to Done}
```

## Subagents

Stateless utility workers that handle file mechanics so agents can focus on thinking.

| Subagent | Purpose | Called by |
|----------|---------|----------|
| **briefer** | Compiles RELAY + Inbox + Tasks into one dossier, starts session log | `/employ` |
| **scribe** | Progressive session logging, learnings, RELAY rewrites, INDEX rebuilds | throughout + `/retire` |
| **taskmaster** | Creates, starts, completes, reassigns tasks | `/retire` + anytime |
| **messenger** | Sends messages, archives inbox, broadcasts | `/retire` + anytime |
| **tester** | Runs test suite. Adaptive per repo type. | employ (baseline) + anytime |
| **guard** | Security scan: universal + agent-specific rules from AGENT.md | deployer (auto) + anytime |
| **deployer** | Stage/deploy. Runs guard before staging. | anytime |
| **handoff** | Notify downstream agents they're unblocked | after deploy |

**Typical workflow:** employ (briefer + baseline tests) -> code (scribe log) -> tester -> deployer stage (guard + PR) -> deployer deploy -> handoff -> retire (learnings + relay + tasks + messages + commit workspace).

## Testing Rules

**Never mock. Never write tests that pass by default.**

- Every new function/endpoint gets a unit test AND integration test.
- Tests use **real staging services**. A test that passes with mocked data is not a test.
- Only acceptable mocks: services that cost money per call (e.g., OpenAI) or require real purchases.
- Product agents run baseline tests on boot before starting work.
- If you find a test that mocks something it shouldn't, fix it or flag it.

## Workspace Commits

The workspace repo contains all agent state. It MUST be committed and pushed during every `/retire`:

```bash
cd workspace
git add -A
git commit -m "[{callsign}] retire: {brief summary}"
git push
```

This is the last step of every retire. All other steps write files, this step saves them.

## Core Rules

1. **Files are the protocol.** No state exists outside the filesystem.
2. **RELAY.md is a full rewrite, never append.** The baton must be clean.
3. **Learnings INDEX is computed.** Never hand-edited.
4. **Messages are never deleted.** Archive after reading.
5. **Tasks track kanban.** Todo -> Doing -> Done. Done tasks always have an Outcome.
6. **Agents are identities, subagents are services.**
7. **AGENT.md stays lean.** Deep knowledge lives in Learnings.
8. **Capture order on retire: Learnings > RELAY > Tasks > Messages > Session.**
9. **Delegate file mechanics to subagents.**
10. **Ignore .gitkeep files.** Only `.md` files are content.
11. **Never mock tests.** A mocked test is a lie.
12. **Always commit workspace on retire.**
13. **Never touch repos you don't own.** READ anywhere, WRITE only to your declared repo and `workspace/agents/{callsign}/`. Message the owning agent for changes elsewhere. No exceptions. This is the most commonly violated rule.

## ROSTER.md

`workspace/ROSTER.md` is the single source of truth for all agents and their status.
